init_text: All of the "#1 Dad" mugs in the world change to show the actual ranking of Dads suddenly.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "No, Dad," she says, "It's just the way it is.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They don't appreciate their parents' sacrifices.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They don't appreciate the fact that their parents are the only reason they're alive.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I'm not going to take this lying down.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She tells me that our daughter is a good kid and that she doesn't deserve to be punished.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "She's a spoiled little brat who doesn't appreciate what she has!"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "It's not about helping her," I say, "It's about punishing her.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "I'm not going to boarding school," McKenzie says.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You're going and you're not coming back until you learn some respect."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I grab her toothbrush and her hairbrush and throw those in there as well.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I grab the barrel and push it away from my face.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I grab the gun and throw it across the room.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I grab my daughter by the throat and throw her against the wall.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You're not going to shoot me," I say.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You're not going to shoot me because you love me.
